Title: An introduction to perturbative and non-perturbative string theory
Authors: Ignatios Antoniadis, Guillaume Ovarlez
Comments: LaTex2e, 17 pages; Lectures given at ``Flavour and Gauge
  Hierarchies'', Cargese, France, 20 Jul.-1 Aug. 1998, and at ``Corfu Summer
  Institute on Elementary Particle Physics'', Kerkyra, Greece, 6-20 Sep. 1998;
  hep-th and CPHT numbers added
Report-no: CPHT-PC719.0699
\\
  In these lectures we give a brief introduction to perturbative and
non-perturbative string theory. The outline is the following:
 1. Introduction to perturbative string theory
  1.1 From point particle to extended objects
  1.2 Free closed and open string spectrum
  1.3 Compactification on a circle and T-duality
  1.4 The Superstring: type IIA and IIB
  1.5 Heterotic string and orbifold compactifications
  1.6 Type I string theory
  1.7 Effective field theories
  References
 2. Introduction to non-perturbative string theory
  2.1 String solitons
  2.2 Non-perturbative string dualities
  2.3 M-theory
  2.4 Effective field theories and duality tests
  References
